value.value: The tergite that is connected to female T9 by muscles.
The ovipositor muscle that arises from the interarticular ridge of the first valvifer and inserts on the second valvifer.

label.value: dorsal ramus of the second valvula

value.value: The area that extends along the dorsal margin of the second valvula, bears the processus articularis anteriorly and the processus musculares on the antero-dorsal region and articulates anteriorly with the second valvifer via the basal articulation.
The anatomical space that is between the left and right olistheters.

label.value: medial conjunctiva of the first valvula

value.value: The conjunctiva that extends medially along the first valvula.

The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical line that extends between the anterior and posterior margins of the dorsal projection of the second valvifer.

label.value: first sclerite of the labial palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distolaterally to the prementum via conjunctiva and muscle.

label.value: second sclerite of the labial palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the first sclerite of the labial palp via conjunctiva and muscle.

label.value: third sclerite of the labial palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the second sclerite of the labial palp via conjunctiva and muscle.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the glossa, paraglossae and labial palps.
The proximal area of the paraglossa that is adjacent to the basiparaglossal brush.
The anteroproximal area of the paraglossa that is covered with long acanthae and corresponds to the ligament connecting the hypopharyngeal button with the basiparaglossal sclerite.
The anteroproximal sclerite of the paraglossa that bears the basiparaglossal brush.
The sclerite that is located medially on the paraglossa and articulates with the anterior glossal plate and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod..
The projection that is located proximolaterally on the anterior glossal plate and articulates with the basiparaglossal sclerite.

label.value: median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate

value.value: The median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate that is parallel with the anteroposterior body axis.
The anatomical cluster of the glossa that is composed of connected annular hairs.
The spine on the distal part of ligula that is connected proximolaterally to the neighboring glossal hair by a carina.
The transverse edge that extends distally on the glossa.
The area of the glossa that is between the distal margin of the prementum and the distal glossal edge.
The area of the glossa that is between the distal glossal edge and the anterior glossal plate.
The row of setae of the glossa that is adjacent to the distal glossal edge.
The seta that is on a process.
The campaniform sensillum of the anterior surface of the glossa that is located proximal to the glossal annuli.
The invagination on the distal hypopharynx that id adjacent to the concavities of the hypopharyngeal rods.
The anterolateral area of the distal hypopharynx that is adjacent with the proximal part of the hypopharyngeal rod proximal to the hypopharyngeal button and is covered with acanthae.
The area that extends between anterior margin of the median wall of the stipes and the lateral margin of the posterior wall of the stipes and the base of the mandible and the labrum.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the spines on the distal margin of the distolateral portion of the principal carina of the stipes.
The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped by the premental carina and overlaps the lateral premental face.
The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped distally by the distomedial stipital carina and overlaps the lateral premental face and the proximal part of the prementum.
The fossa that is located on the cardo and articulates with the cardinal condyle of the cranium.

label.value: fifth sclerite of the maxillary palp

value.value: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.
The sensillum whose cuticular component has one cuticular pore.

label.value: fourth intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the third sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp.
The sclerite that is located on the interstipital area and is connected to the prementum via conjunctiva.

label.value: Stipital articular surface of the postmentum

value.value: The articular surface that articulates with the madial margin of the stipes.
The ridge that is limited laterally by the stipital articular surfaces of the postmentum.
The conjunctiva that is between the postmentum and prementum.
The scrobe of the prementum that is adjacent to and extends lateral to the premental carina and accommodates the medial part of the posterior stipital sclerite.
The sclerite that receives the site of insertions of the dorsal and ventral premento-salivarial muscles and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod.
The area that is resilin rich.
The carinae that radiates from the posterior glossal plate towards the apical glossal setae.
The anterior invagination of the labium that is adjacent with the distal end of the salivarium and separates the glossa proximally from the distal hypopharynx and the paraglossae.
The sclerite that is located distally on the paraglossa.
The anatomical cluster of the paraglossa that is composed of connected annular hairs.
The bent area of the hypopharyngeal rod that receives the site of insertion of the posterior tentorio-premental muscle.
The gland that empties anterior to the prementum.
The duct that leads from the salivary gland.

label.value: first intrinsic muscle of the labial palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the first sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the second sclerite of the labial palp.

label.value: second intrinsic muscle of the labial palp

value.value: The muscle that arises from the second sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the labial palp.
